HEADWORD: Suffruticose
<hw>Suf*fru"ti*cose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>suf-</ets> + <ets>fruticose</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Woody in the lower part of the stem, but with the yearly branches
herbaceous, as sage, thyme, hyssop, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

